main event: Two saucer-shaped, silver-colored objects were observed flying over Washington, Missouri at a high rate of speed on July 25, 1964.
interesting points: The objects were estimated to be approximately 20-30 feet in diameter and were observed at an altitude of around 5,000 feet.
The objects traveled at a very high speed and disappeared quickly, making it impossible for the witnesses to obtain any photographs.
The sighting was observed by Mrs. Linda Jaegers and the report author, who considered the sighting to be authentic and extremely puzzling.
The witnesses were within good viewing range and had an excellent opportunity to observe the objects closely.
The objects' movements, such as suddenly speeding up and slowing down, as well as changing direction, were described as puzzling.
witnesses: Mrs. Linda Jaegers and the report author
